  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "RTE uses OS for communication between"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "OS Applications",
        "Synchronization between the cores",
        "Sending events from one core to other"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "RTE generates the code that uses above OS functionality automatically"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Sender-Receiver Communication"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "1:n or n:1 communication. Senders provides the data and Receiver receives the data"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Receiver Mode:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Implicit data read access - when the receiver’s runnable executes it shall have access to a “copy” of the data that remains unchanged during the execution of the runnable",
        "Explicit data read access - the RTE generator creates a non-blocking API call to enable a receiver to poll (and read) data",
        "wake up of wait point - the RTE generator creates a blocking API call that the receiver invokes to read data",
        "activation of runnable entity - the receiving runnable entity is invoked automatically by the RTE whenever new data is available"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Rte%20Multicore%20Handling/image2022-8-18_21-23-48.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Rte Multicore Handling/image2022-8-18_21-23-48.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Rte_Read / Rte_Write (Simple Data Transfer)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "At Sender side:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Sender writes data to using Rte_Write",
        "Rte writes data to shared memory using OS IOC_Write(Inter OS communication) Call",
        "Rte sets an event to Receiver core to inform it has sent the data"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "At Receiver side:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Event set by Sender will trigger Rte_read API",
        "Rte reads data from Shared memory using IOC_Read API"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/Rte%20Multicore%20Handling/image2022-8-18_21-24-42.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/Rte Multicore Handling/image2022-8-18_21-24-42.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Rte_Receive/Rte_Send (Queued transfer of data)"
    },
